### 🔴 High Priority Issues

#### 1. No Global Error Handling Middleware
If any route throws an unhandled error, Express will send the full stack trace to the client, leaking internal details (file paths, dependency versions, etc.).

```js
// Add at the end, before app.listen()
app.use((err, req, res, next) => {
  console.error(err.stack);
